abstract: The attempt to exclude trans women from the ranks of women reinforces the dangerous idea that there is a right way to be female.
snippet: The attempt to exclude trans women from the ranks of women reinforces the dangerous idea that there is a right way to be female.
lead_paragraph: Who counts as a woman? Is there some set of core experiences distinctive of womanhood, some shared set of adventures and exploits that every woman will encounter on her journey from diapers to the grave? The recent debates over the experiences of trans women gives us new reason to return to a question feminists have been grappling with for decades.

lead_paragraph: Sometimes, it turns out, writers aren’t who you thought they were — at all.

abstract: A trade deal could result in China promising to buy hundreds of billions of dollars of American products. It could further cement Beijing’s role in the economy.
snippet: A trade deal could result in China promising to buy hundreds of billions of dollars of American products. It could further cement Beijing’s role in the economy.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — At the heart of President Trump’s negotiations with China is a troubling contradiction: The United States wants to use the trade talks to encourage the country to adopt a more market-oriented economy. But a key element of a prospective deal may end up reinforcing the economic power of the Chinese state.

abstract: Ghosts! Billygoats! Lazy men and thirsty thieves! All these stories — and more like them — as they were dutifully reported in the late 1800s and early 1900s.
snippet: Ghosts! Billygoats! Lazy men and thirsty thieves! All these stories — and more like them — as they were dutifully reported in the late 1800s and early 1900s.
lead_paragraph: The headlines you’ll see below are bizarre. But the articles, all of which once appeared in the pages of The New York Times, are even more so.

abstract: A racist caricature from 19th-century minstrel theater still haunts America.
snippet: A racist caricature from 19th-century minstrel theater still haunts America.
lead_paragraph: Nineteenth-century minstrel entertainers  spawned a racist caricature that endures to this day when they darkened their faces to portray black people as grinning, dancing simpletons.

abstract: In the 1980s and ’90s, the novelist was seen as a literary bad boy and the voice of his generation. Now 55, he’s about to publish his first book in nine years.
snippet: In the 1980s and ’90s, the novelist was seen as a literary bad boy and the voice of his generation. Now 55, he’s about to publish his first book in nine years.
lead_paragraph: Bret Easton Ellis is no stranger to bad publicity. Ever since his 1985 debut, “Less Than Zero,” made him a literary sensation, his violently nihilistic fiction and his politically incorrect public persona have earned him as much fury as acclaim. And after three decades, five subsequent novels and a story collection, a podcast and more than a handful of media spats, Ellis still has more to say. On April 16, he will publish his first book in nine years — and his nonfiction debut — an essay collection called “White.” Not everybody is going to like it. He doesn’t care.

headline_main: Bret Easton Ellis Has Calmed Down. He Thinks You Should, Too.

abstract: Several 2020 presidential candidates are focused on attracting small donors to prove grass-roots appeal, but are also privately courting major donors whose money helps pay campaign bills.
snippet: Several 2020 presidential candidates are focused on attracting small donors to prove grass-roots appeal, but are also privately courting major donors whose money helps pay campaign bills.
lead_paragraph: Senator Cory Booker spun through a San Francisco fund-raiser hosted on Friday afternoon by high-tech titans and wealthy venture capitalists, including the investor Ron Conway. That evening, in New York, Senator Kirsten Gillibrand gathered donations at the Upper West Side home of Matthew Mallow, a vice chairman of the investment giant BlackRock.

abstract: America’s top diplomat stands out in the Trump administration for brazenly inserting his evangelical Christian beliefs into discussions of foreign policy.
snippet: America’s top diplomat stands out in the Trump administration for brazenly inserting his evangelical Christian beliefs into discussions of foreign policy.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — When Secretary of State Mike Pompeo sat down for an interview with the Christian Broadcasting Network in a hotel in Jerusalem earlier this month, he made a remark that was perhaps the most revelatory of any in his nearly one year in office.

headline_main: The Rapture and the Real World: Mike Pompeo Blends Beliefs and Policy
headline_print_headline: The Rapture and the Real World: Pompeo Mixes Beliefs and Policy

abstract: A look back through the decades shows the successes and challenges of a divisive social policy.
snippet: A look back through the decades shows the successes and challenges of a divisive social policy.
lead_paragraph: On cold mornings, Les Goodson shows up early outside the University Club, on a wealthy stretch of Fifth Avenue in Manhattan, and races two panhandlers he has nicknamed Catman and Pimp-the-Baby for a warm spot in front of a steam vent. He launches into “Take Five” on his saxophone, leaving his case open for bills and coins.
